$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\X.Y

This → Windows/registry/tree-structure/key[registry key] contains sub keys for the installed → Microsoft/Office products or common features, such as:
  • → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Excel[`Excel`]
  • → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Outlook[`Outlook`]
  • → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Word[`Word`]
  • → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Common[`Common`]
  • → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/PowerQuery[`PowerQuery`]
  • → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Registration[`Registration`]

The version number of an installed Office pplication (that is: the `X.Y` in the registry key) can be found with → development/languages/VBA[VBA] and the → Microsoft/Office/Object-Model/Application#ms-object-model-applicaion-version[`version`] property of the
corresponding → Microsoft/Office/Object-Model/Application[`application`] object, for example by typing the following expression into the
→ Microsoft/Office/Visual-Basic-Editor/Immediate-Window[immediate window]:
code {
? application.version
code }


sa:

  → Microsoft/Office/versions#office-determine-version[Determine Office Version without opening an Office application]

  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office
